  <name>DVD Ripper</name>
  <summary>Rip episodic DVDs with GPU-accelerated encoding</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      A modern DVD ripping application designed for Linux desktops and the Steam Deck.
      Rip episodic DVDs, detect duplicates, merge chronologically, and encode to MP4
      with hardware-accelerated AMD VAAPI encoding.
    </p>
    <p>Features:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>AMD VAAPI GPU encoding (H.264, HEVC, AV1)</li>
      <li>Automatic duplicate detection and removal</li>
      <li>Chronological episode merging</li>
      <li>Deinterlacing and video cleanup</li>
      <li>Subtitle support (soft or burned-in)</li>
      <li>Upscaling to 720p/1080p/1440p/4K</li>
      <li>Play All mode for single-file output</li>
      <li>ISO and VIDEO_TS folder support</li>
      <li>Native GTK4/Libadwaita interface</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.github.CyDragonReborn.Steam-Deck-DVD-Ripper.desktop</launchable>
  <url type="homepage">https://github.com/CyDragonReborn/Steam-Deck-DVD-Ripper</url>
